A similar to Cisco's mrinfo multicast routing information utility for GNU/Linux.
Written for fun and educational purposes only.

Build:
    $make

Dependencies:
    libpcap - responses listener

Usage:
    Simple probe.
	# ./mrinfo <target>
    5 seconds timeout
	# ./mrinfo -t 5<target>
    show help
	$ ./mrinfo -h

Output:
    $ sudo ./mrinfo 192.168.2.2
    192.168.2.2 [Version  12.4] [Flags: PM]:
     192.168.2.2 -> 192.168.2.4 [1/0]
     192.168.2.2 -> 192.168.2.3 [1/0]
     192.168.13.1 -> 192.168.13.3 [1/0]

License:
